---  
description: Use when setting Sitecore field values through MCP, especially General Link XML, Image XML, checkbox values, rich text, and date formats.  
alwaysApply: false  
---  
  
When setting values via MCP, follow Sitecore storage formats exactly.  
  
Field formats:  
- Single-Line Text / Multi-Line Text: plain string  
- Rich Text: HTML string  
- Checkbox: `"1"` for true, `""` for false  
- Date / DateTime: ISO style Sitecore string like `20250217T120000Z`  
- Image: raw image XML string  
- General Link: raw Sitecore link XML string  
  
General Link rules:  
- Pass the full XML string as a normal string value.  
- Include all expected attributes.  
- Do not manually escape quotes with backslashes.  
- Keep attribute order consistent.  
  
Internal link example:  
`<link text="" anchor="" linktype="internal" class="" title="" target="" querystring="" id="{ITEM-GUID}" />`  
  
External link example:  
`<link text="Visit site" anchor="" linktype="external" class="" title="" target="_blank" querystring="" url="https://example.com" />`  
  
Image example:  
`<image mediaid="{MEDIA-ITEM-GUID}" />`  
  
Update tool guidance:  
- Use `update_content` for site-scoped content items.  
- Use `update_fields_on_content_item` for templates, renderings, and non-site-scoped items.  